import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['fertility'].plot(kind='hist', bins=20, color='green', alpha=0.5)
    plt.axvline(data['fertility'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean')
    plt.axvline(data['fertility'].median(), color='blue', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of fertility across all countries?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    plt.scatter(data['fertility'], data['life_expect'])
    plt.xlabel('Fertility')
    plt.ylabel('Life Expectancy')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between fertility and life expectancy?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data.groupby('country')['fertility'].mean().reset_index()
    data = data.sort_values(by='fertility', ascending=False)
    plt.bar(data['country'], data['fertility'])
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.title('What is the average fertility rate in each country?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['life_expect'] = pd.to_datetime(data['life_expect'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    plt.hist(data['life_expect'].dropna(), bins=20, color='green')
    plt.axvline(data['life_expect'].mean(), color='red', label='Mean: {:.2f}'.format(data['life_expect'].mean()))
    plt.axvline(data['life_expect'].median(), color='blue', label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['life_expect'].median()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of life expectancy across all countries?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['fertility'].plot(kind='box', color='red', label='Actual fertility')
    data['n_fertility'].plot(kind='box', color='blue', label='Normalized fertility')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the difference between the normalized and actual fertility rates?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
